A 31-year-old man from Mettur in Salem district, who worked as a car driver in Coimbatore and stole money and valuables from many cars over the last one year, was nabbed by the city police on Thursday.According to the police, he was found to be involved in at least seven such incidents and inquires were under way to find out if he was involved in more incidents. The accused, A. Radhakrishnan, worked as a temporary driver in many private companies. It was found that he committed the offence alone and kept the valuables in his house in Salem, and at a relativeâ€™s place.